A strong presence of Italian publishers at the international exhibition of the Frankfurt book.
More than three hundred Italian publishers will be present at the 60th edition of the Buchmesse, the most important international meeting for the exchange of rights.
The international exhibition of the Frankfurt book is expected for this edition more than 7,000 exhibitors from 102 different countries that will occupy the 171,790 square meters of the exhibition with more than 403,000 titles on display and with Turkey as guest of honor.
It will be the undersecretary of the Ministry of goods and cultural activities Francisco Maria Giro to represent the Italian government at the opening ceremony of the Italian Pavilion: Italy will be institutionally and effectively present with a point Italy - 264 square meters of exhibition space.
A print meeting will follow in Room Struktur in Hall 5.0 of the Buchmesse: this will be the occasion to present numbers, trends and prospects on the state of publishing in Italy.
According to the data, the weight of books by foreign authors progressively decreases over the total of Italian production, and in particular that for adults and adolescents.
Steve Fossett's plane missing a year ago
The remains of Steve Fossett’s plane, the millionaire who disappeared on September 3, 2007, were found while flying over the Nevada desert.
The debris has been found on a plateau at 3,000 meters above sea level, in the Mammoth Lakes area of the Nevada Range, on the California-Nevada border.
Inside the plane, there were no human remains.
“The plane has been located, we have sent a squadron, and now we have confirmation that it is the very thing that Steve Fossett was flying about on the day of his disappearance,” Anderson said.
The commissioner said no human remains were found either on the plane or in the vicinity.
The 63-year-old millionaire was put to death in February.
The U.S. Transportation Security Office said a few hours after the sighting of the remains, a squadron of investigators had been sent to identify the aircraft: it was the Bellanca 8kcab, which had been dispersed since September 3, 2007, when Fossett took off from Yerington, Nevada, for a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, still in California, not far from the Nevada border, some personal remains of Fossett have been found by a couple near their Mammoth Lakes home.
These are two documents named after Fossett, the two issued by the Illinois Federal Aviation Administration, cash and a sweatshirt.
Fossett's search had been interrupted a month after his disappearance.
The millionaire had earned a place in history thanks to a long series of firsts.
By 2002, at the sixth attempt, he had become the first man to complete the world tour in a hot air balloon: two solitary weeks of flight.
Three years later he had travelled the world by plane and without a stopover.
Among his records, also that for having flown at 15,445 meters high, over the Andes, but with a co-pilot.
Glk, the advertising you don't expect
An out-of-the-box Suv with an original, well-established design with defined lines and determined angles.
This is, in short, Glk’s latest addition to the “compact” all-terrain vans in the starhouse with which Mercedes-Benz has sought to give a window of novelty in this sector.
Proper for the content out of the traditional, will be unexpected and unconventional, the communication that will accompany the launch of the Glk suv, available in the Mercedes-Benz showrooms from next October 17th.
The advertising campaign that accompanied the debut of the new car will launch an unprecedented mode of communication through a 3D advertising campaign, used for the first time in Italy by an automotive brand.
A project with maxi-posters, articulated in three different phases, that dominated the central street of the Milanese shopping, Como Avenue, until November 15.
The first phase of this new type of communication will start with the presentation of the car in a stereoscopic version and thanks to special glasses distributed on the avenue How it will be possible to see the new SUV in almost real dimensions and in three-dimensional format.
Indeed, looking at the images will have the impression that the car comes out of the poster.
Subsequently, through the use of the innovative Elumina8 technology, the new Glk will be illuminated at different times in all its details, to be recomposed into a single image.
Undoubtedly Mercedes with this advertising is trying to introduce something new in the stereotype of automotive communication.
Will this formula be able to capture the interest of future buyers? we will see.
